      "output": "Message Formatting and Chat History | Aider-AI/aider | DeepWiki\n\nLoading...\n\nIndex your code with Devin\n\n[DeepWiki](/)\n\n[DeepWiki](/)\n\n[Aider-AI/aider](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider \"Open repository\")\n\nIndex your code with\n\nDevin\n\nEdit WikiShare\n\nLoading...\n\nLast indexed: 23 May 2026 ([5dc949](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/commits/5dc9490b))\n\n-   [Overview](/Aider-AI/aider/1-overview)\n-   [Getting Started](/Aider-AI/aider/1.1-getting-started)\n-   [Key Concepts and Terminology](/Aider-AI/aider/1.2-key-concepts-and-terminology)\n-   [Core Architecture](/Aider-AI/aider/2-core-architecture)\n-   [Application Entry Point and Main Loop](/Aider-AI/aider/2.1-application-entry-point-and-main-loop)\n-   [Coder Orchestration System](/Aider-AI/aider/2.2-coder-orchestration-system)\n-   [Commands and User Interactions](/Aider-AI/aider/2.3-commands-and-user-interactions)\n-   [Model Management and LLM Integration](/Aider-AI/aider/2.4-model-management-and-llm-integration)\n-   [Input/Output and Terminal Interface](/Aider-AI/aider/2.5-inputoutput-and-terminal-interface)\n-   [Edit Strategies and Code Modification](/Aider-AI/aider/3-edit-strategies-and-code-modification)\n-   [Edit Format Implementations](/Aider-AI/aider/3.1-edit-format-implementations)\n-   [Search and Replace Logic](/Aider-AI/aider/3.2-search-and-replace-logic)\n-   [Diff Generation and Display](/Aider-AI/aider/3.3-diff-generation-and-display)\n-   [Prompt Engineering and Templates](/Aider-AI/aider/3.4-prompt-engineering-and-templates)\n-   [Message Formatting and Chat History](/Aider-AI/aider/3.5-message-formatting-and-chat-history)\n-   [Repository Understanding and Context](/Aider-AI/aider/4-repository-understanding-and-context)\n-   [Repository Mapping System](/Aider-AI/aider/4.1-repository-mapping-system)\n-   [File Management and Tracking](/Aider-AI/aider/4.2-file-management-and-tracking)\n-   [Git Integration and Version Control](/Aider-AI/aider/4.3-git-integration-and-version-control)\n-   [File Watching and AI Comments](/Aider-AI/aider/4.4-file-watching-and-ai-comments)\n-   [Code Quality and Linting](/Aider-AI/aider/4.5-code-quality-and-linting)\n-   [User Interaction Modes](/Aider-AI/aider/5-user-interaction-modes)\n-   [Command Line Interface](/Aider-AI/aider/5.1-command-line-interface)\n-   [Streamlit Web GUI](/Aider-AI/aider/5.2-streamlit-web-gui)\n-   [Voice-to-Code Mode](/Aider-AI/aider/5.3-voice-to-code-mode)\n-   [Copy/Paste Integration with Web Chat UIs](/Aider-AI/aider/5.4-copypaste-integration-with-web-chat-uis)\n-   [Architect Mode](/Aider-AI/aider/5.5-architect-mode)\n-   [Web Content Integration](/Aider-AI/aider/6-web-content-integration)\n-   [Web Scraping Architecture](/Aider-AI/aider/6.1-web-scraping-architecture)\n-   [SSL Verification Configuration](/Aider-AI/aider/6.2-ssl-verification-configuration)\n-   [Model Configuration and Capabilities](/Aider-AI/aider/7-model-configuration-and-capabilities)\n-   [Model Settings and Behavioral Configuration](/Aider-AI/aider/7.1-model-settings-and-behavioral-configuration)\n-   [Model Metadata and Technical Capabilities](/Aider-AI/aider/7.2-model-metadata-and-technical-capabilities)\n-   [Multi-Provider LLM Integration](/Aider-AI/aider/7.3-multi-provider-llm-integration)\n-   [Three-Tier Model System](/Aider-AI/aider/7.4-three-tier-model-system)\n-   [Reasoning and Thinking Token Configuration](/Aider-AI/aider/7.5-reasoning-and-thinking-token-configuration)\n-   [Development and Quality Assurance](/Aider-AI/aider/8-development-and-quality-assurance)\n-   [Benchmarking System Architecture](/Aider-AI/aider/8.1-benchmarking-system-architecture)\n-   [Testing Infrastructure](/Aider-AI/aider/8.2-testing-infrastructure)\n-   [Performance Leaderboards](/Aider-AI/aider/8.3-performance-leaderboards)\n-   [Configuration and Deployment](/Aider-AI/aider/9-configuration-and-deployment)\n-   [Configuration System](/Aider-AI/aider/9.1-configuration-system)\n-   [Dependency Management](/Aider-AI/aider/9.2-dependency-management)\n-   [Build and Version Management](/Aider-AI/aider/9.3-build-and-version-management)\n-   [Utilities and Supporting Systems](/Aider-AI/aider/10-utilities-and-supporting-systems)\n-   [Core Utility Functions](/Aider-AI/aider/10.1-core-utility-functions)\n-   [Error Reporting and Version Checking](/Aider-AI/aider/10.2-error-reporting-and-version-checking)\n-   [Package Installation Utilities](/Aider-AI/aider/10.3-package-installation-utilities)\n-   [Help and Documentation System](/Aider-AI/aider/11-help-and-documentation-system)\n-   [Help System Architecture](/Aider-AI/aider/11.1-help-system-architecture)\n-   [HelpCoder and Context Assembly](/Aider-AI/aider/11.2-helpcoder-and-context-assembly)\n-   [Analytics and Self-Improvement](/Aider-AI/aider/12-analytics-and-self-improvement)\n-   [Usage Analytics](/Aider-AI/aider/12.1-usage-analytics)\n-   [Self-Referential Development Metrics](/Aider-AI/aider/12.2-self-referential-development-metrics)\n-   [Glossary](/Aider-AI/aider/13-glossary)\n\nMenu\n\n# Message Formatting and Chat History\n\nRelevant source files\n\n-   [aider/coders/udiff\\_simple.py](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/coders/udiff_simple.py)\n-   [aider/coders/udiff\\_simple\\_prompts.py](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/coders/udiff_simple_prompts.py)\n-   [aider/history.py](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/history.py)\n-   [aider/prompts.py](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/prompts.py)\n-   [aider/sendchat.py](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/sendchat.py)\n-   [tests/basic/test\\_history.py](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/tests/basic/test_history.py)\n-   [tests/basic/test\\_repo.py](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/tests/basic/test_repo.py)\n-   [tests/basic/test\\_sendchat.py](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/tests/basic/test_sendchat.py)\n-   [tests/scrape/test\\_playwright\\_disable.py](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/tests/scrape/test_playwright_disable.py)\n\nThis document explains how Aider formats messages before sending them to LLMs and manages conversation history over extended sessions. It covers the message structure, role alternation requirements, chat history accumulation, and automatic summarization via `ChatSummary`.\n\nFor information about the actual prompts and templates used in messages, see [aider/prompts.py](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/prompts.py) For model-specific message handling and token counting, see [aider/models.py](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/models.py)\n\n## Message Structure and Layers\n\nAider constructs a layered message structure before each LLM API call. Messages are assembled from multiple sources and formatted into a standardized sequence that provides the LLM with system instructions, repository context, conversation history, and the current user request.\n\n### Natural Language Space to Code Entity Space: Message Assembly\n\nThe following diagram maps the logical parts of a chat message to the internal code methods and variables that generate them.\n\n**Sources:** [aider/coders/base\\_coder.py750-815](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/coders/base_coder.py#L750-L815) [aider/sendchat.py5-61](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/sendchat.py#L5-L61)\n\n### System Messages\n\nSystem messages contain the core instructions that define the LLM's behavior. These are formatted via `fmt_system_prompt()` and include:\n\n-   **Main system prompt**: Instructions for the edit format, coding style, and general behavior.\n-   **System reminder**: Reinforces key instructions to maintain consistency.\n\nSystem messages are constructed fresh for each request and cannot be cached between messages. **Sources:** [aider/coders/base\\_coder.py452-461](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/coders/base_coder.py#L452-L461)\n\n### Context Messages\n\nContext messages provide the LLM with information about the codebase and files. These are structured as user/assistant pairs to maintain role alternation:\n\nContext Type\n\nUser Message Content\n\nAssistant Reply\n\n**Repository Map**\n\n`repo_content_prefix` + ranked tags from `get_repo_map()`\n\n\"Ok, I won't try and edit those files without asking first.\"\n\n**Read-Only Files**\n\n`read_only_files_prefix` + file contents\n\n\"Ok, I will use these files as references.\"\n\n**Chat Files**\n\n`files_content_prefix` + editable file contents\n\n`files_content_assistant_reply` or \"Ok.\"\n\n**Sources:** [aider/coders/base\\_coder.py750-815](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/coders/base_coder.py#L750-L815)\n\n## Message Role Alternation\n\nLLM APIs (especially Anthropic and some OpenAI-compatible providers) require messages to alternate between `user` and `assistant` roles. Aider enforces this through validation and automatic correction in `aider/sendchat.py`.\n\n**Sources:** [aider/sendchat.py5-61](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/sendchat.py#L5-L61)\n\n### sanity\\_check\\_messages()\n\nValidates that messages properly alternate between `user` and `assistant` roles:\n\n-   Ignores `system` messages when checking alternation [aider/sendchat.py15-16](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/sendchat.py#L15-L16)\n-   Verifies that the last non-system message is from the `user` [aider/sendchat.py26](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/sendchat.py#L26-L26)\n-   Raises `ValueError` if validation fails, including a formatted dump of the messages [aider/sendchat.py18-20](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/sendchat.py#L18-L20)\n\n**Sources:** [aider/sendchat.py5-26](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/sendchat.py#L5-L26)\n\n### ensure\\_alternating\\_roles()\n\nAutomatically fixes messages with consecutive same-role entries by inserting empty \"opposite role\" messages:\n\n-   If two consecutive `user` messages are found, it inserts `{\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": \"\"}` [aider/sendchat.py53-54](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/sendchat.py#L53-L54)\n-   If two consecutive `assistant` messages are found, it inserts `{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"\"}` [aider/sendchat.py55-56](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/sendchat.py#L55-L56)\n\n**Sources:** [aider/sendchat.py29-61](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/sendchat.py#L29-L61)\n\n## Chat History Management and Summarization\n\nThe `ChatSummary` class handles the logic for reducing the size of the conversation history while preserving critical context.\n\n### The Summarization Algorithm\n\nWhen history exceeds `max_tokens`, `ChatSummary` performs the following:\n\n1.  **Tokenization**: It calculates the token count for each message using the model's `token_count` method [aider/history.py20-25](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/history.py#L20-L25)\n2.  **Splitting**: It splits the messages into a \"head\" (older messages) and a \"tail\" (recent messages). It attempts to keep roughly half of `max_tokens` for the tail [aider/history.py48-57](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/history.py#L48-L57)\n3.  **Head Summarization**: The head is summarized into a single user message using the `summarize_all()` method [aider/history.py87](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/history.py#L87-L87)\n4.  **Recursive Refinement**: If the combined summary and tail are still too large, it recurses via `summarize_real()` [aider/history.py96](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/history.py#L96-L96)\n\n### summarize\\_all()\n\nThis method performs the actual LLM call to generate the summary:\n\n-   It formats the messages into a plain text representation prefixed with `# USER` or `# ASSISTANT` [aider/history.py99-108](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/history.py#L99-L108)\n-   It uses `prompts.summarize` as the system instruction [aider/history.py110](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/history.py#L110-L110)\n-   The prompt instructs the LLM to write in the first person as the user, referencing the assistant as \"you\" [aider/prompts.py55-58](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/prompts.py#L55-L58)\n-   It requires the inclusion of function names, libraries, and filenames referenced in code blocks [aider/prompts.py51-52](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/prompts.py#L51-L52)\n\n**Sources:** [aider/history.py7-124](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/history.py#L7-L124) [aider/prompts.py46-61](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/prompts.py#L46-L61)\n\n### Chat History Summarization Flow\n\nThe following diagram maps the summarization process to specific functions in `aider/history.py`.\n\n**Sources:** [aider/history.py7-124](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/history.py#L7-L124) [aider/prompts.py46-61](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/prompts.py#L46-L61)\n\n## Message Content Formatting\n\n### File Content Formatting\n\nFiles are formatted with fencing characters to clearly delimit content. The fence characters are selected to avoid conflicts with content.\n\n### Edit Format Changes\n\nWhen switching edit formats (e.g., via `/model`), old assistant messages may be summarized to prevent the LLM from being confused by previous structural instructions.\n\n**Sources:** [aider/coders/base\\_coder.py156-168](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/coders/base_coder.py#L156-L168)\n\n### Commit Message Generation\n\nAider uses the same messaging infrastructure to generate commit messages. The `GitRepo.get_commit_message` method sends a list of messages to the LLM containing the `commit_system` prompt and the git diff [aider/prompts.py8-22](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/prompts.py#L8-L22)\n\n**Sources:** [aider/prompts.py8-22](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/aider/prompts.py#L8-L22) [tests/basic/test\\_repo.py131-154](https://github.com/Aider-AI/aider/blob/5dc9490b/tests/basic/test_repo.py#L131-L154)\n\nDismiss\n\nRefresh this wiki\n\nEnter email to refresh\n\n### On this page\n\n-   [Message Formatting and Chat History](#message-formatting-and-chat-history)\n-   [Message Structure and Layers](#message-structure-and-layers)\n-   [Natural Language Space to Code Entity Space: Message Assembly](#natural-language-space-to-code-entity-space-message-assembly)\n-   [System Messages](#system-messages)\n-   [Context Messages](#context-messages)\n-   [Message Role Alternation](#message-role-alternation)\n-   [sanity\\_check\\_messages()](#sanity_check_messages)\n-   [ensure\\_alternating\\_roles()](#ensure_alternating_roles)\n-   [Chat History Management and Summarization](#chat-history-management-and-summarization)\n-   [The Summarization Algorithm](#the-summarization-algorithm)\n-   [summarize\\_all()](#summarize_all)\n-   [Chat History Summarization Flow](#chat-history-summarization-flow)\n-   [Message Content Formatting](#message-content-formatting)\n-   [File Content Formatting](#file-content-formatting)\n-   [Edit Format Changes](#edit-format-changes)\n-   [Commit Message Generation](#commit-message-generation)",
      "status": "success",
