      "text": "Now I have comprehensive information to provide a detailed summary. Here is my complete research report:\n\n---\n\n## Aider Session Storage: Complete Technical Summary\n\n### 1. Where Session Data Is Stored (File Paths)\n\nAider stores session-related data in **three main locations**:\n\n#### A. Chat History (Markdown Log)\n- **Path:** `<git_root>/.aider.chat.history.md`\n- **Fallback:** `./.aider.chat.history.md` (if no git root)\n- **Source code:** `aider/args.py` defines:\n  ```python\n  default_chat_history_file = (\n      os.path.join(git_root, \".aider.chat.history.md\") if git_root else \".aider.chat.history.md\"\n  )\n  ```\n- **Configurable via:** `--chat-history-file` CLI flag or `AIDER_CHAT_HISTORY_FILE` env var\n\n#### B. Input History (Prompt Toolkit)\n- **Path:** `<git_root>/.aider.input.history`\n- **Fallback:** `./.aider.input.history` (if no git root)\n- **Configurable via:** `--input-history-file` CLI flag or `AIDER_INPUT_HISTORY_FILE` env var\n\n#### C. LLM Conversation Log (Optional)\n- **Path:** Custom path specified by user (e.g., `.aider.llm.history`)\n- **Enabled via:** `--llm-history-file` CLI flag\n\n#### D. Repository Map Cache (SQLite)\n- **Path:** `<git_root>/.aider.tags.cache.v4/`\n- **Format:** SQLite database via `diskcache` library\n- **Source code:** `aider/repomap.py`:\n  ```python\n  TAGS_CACHE_DIR = f\".aider.tags.cache.v{CACHE_VERSION}\"\n  ```\n\n#### E. User-Level Config/Data Directory\n- **Path:** `~/.aider/`\n  - `~/.aider/analytics.json` - Analytics UUID and opt-in state\n  - `~/.aider/oauth-keys.env` - OAuth-obtained API keys\n  - `~/.aider/installs.json` - Track first-run per version/executable\n  - `~/.aider/caches/` - Cache directory root (model pricing, version check, help index)\n\n---\n\n### 2. Storage Format\n\nAider uses **multiple storage formats** depending on the data type:\n\n| Data Type | Format | Description |\n|-----------|--------|-------------|\n| **Chat History Log** | **Markdown** (`.md`) | Human-readable transcript of the session |\n| **Input History** | **Prompt Toolkit FileHistory** | Binary/text format for command-line input history |\n| **LLM Conversation Log** | **Custom text format** | Full conversation with the LLM |\n| **Repository Map Cache** | **SQLite** (via `diskcache`) | Parsed tree-sitter tags and file metadata |\n| **Configuration** | **YAML** (`.aider.conf.yml`) | Configuration settings |\n| **Environment Variables** | **Dotenv** (`.env`) | API keys and environment variables |\n\n**Important distinction:** Unlike Claude Code (which uses JSONL) or OpenCode (which uses SQLite for sessions), Aider's primary chat history is stored as a **Markdown file**, not a structured database format.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Schema/Structure of Session Data\n\n#### A. Chat History Markdown Format (`.aider.chat.history.md`)\n\nThe chat history is a **Markdown transcript** that logs the full session. It is structured as:\n\n```markdown\n# Chat History\n\n## [Timestamp]\n\n### User\n[User message content]\n\n### Assistant\n[Assistant response with code blocks, diffs, etc.]\n\n### User\n[Next user message]\n\n### Assistant\n[Next assistant response]\n```\n\n**Key characteristics:**\n- Append-only log format\n- Not loaded into future sessions automatically -- it is a reference log, not active memory\n- Contains the full conversation including code edits, diffs, and tool outputs\n- Human-readable and editable\n\n#### B. In-Memory Message Structure (for LLM API calls)\n\nDuring a session, Aider maintains an in-memory message list with this structure:\n\n```python\n{\n    \"role\": \"system\" | \"user\" | \"assistant\",\n    \"content\": \"string\"\n}\n```\n\n**Message roles:**\n- `system` - System prompts (instructions, reminders)\n- `user` - User messages, context (repo map, file contents), tool results\n- `assistant` - LLM responses, code edits, file modifications\n\n**Context message types (as user/assistant pairs):**\n\n| Context Type | User Message Content | Assistant Reply |\n|--------------|---------------------|-----------------|\n| **Repository Map** | `repo_content_prefix` + ranked tags | \"Ok, I won't try and edit those files without asking first.\" |\n| **Read-Only Files** | `read_only_files_prefix` + file contents | \"Ok, I will use these files as references.\" |\n| **Chat Files** | `files_content_prefix` + editable file contents | `files_content_assistant_reply` or \"Ok.\" |\n| **Images** | Base64-encoded images with filenames | \"Ok.\" or \"Ok, I will use these images as references.\" |\n\n#### C. Chat Summarization Schema\n\nWhen chat history exceeds `max_tokens`, the `ChatSummary` class (in `aider/history.py`) performs summarization:\n\n```python\nclass ChatSummary:\n    def __init__(self, models=None, max_tokens=1024):\n        self.models = models  # List of Model objects\n        self.max_tokens = max_tokens\n        self.token_count = self.models[0].token_count\n```\n\n**Summarization algorithm:**\n1. Tokenize all messages\n2. Split into \"head\" (older) and \"tail\" (recent) messages\n3. Summarize the head into a single user message using the LLM\n4. Combine summary + tail\n5. Recurse if still too large (max depth: 3)\n\n**Summary format:**\n```python\n# USER\n[user message content]\n\n# ASSISTANT\n[assistant message content]\n```\n\nThe summary is prefixed with a predefined string from `prompts.summary_prefix`.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Available Fields and Data\n\n#### A. Chat History Fields (in-memory during session)\n\n| Field | Description |\n|-------|-------------|\n| `role` | Message role: \"system\", \"user\", or \"assistant\" |\n| `content` | Message content (text, code, diffs) |\n\n**Additional context tracked during session:**\n- **Editable files** - Files added to chat for modification\n- **Read-only files** - Files added as reference context\n- **Repository map** - Skeleton of codebase structure\n- **File contents** - Full contents of files in chat\n- **Git diff** - Changes made during the session\n- **Commit messages** - Auto-generated or user-specified\n\n#### B. LLM History File Fields (when `--llm-history-file` is set)\n\nContains the full conversation with the LLM including:\n- All system prompts\n- All user messages\n- All assistant responses\n- Token counts and cost information\n- Timestamps\n\n#### C. Input History Fields (`.aider.input.history`)\n\n- Previous user inputs/commands\n- Prompt toolkit's FileHistory format\n\n#### D. Tag Cache Fields (`.aider.tags.cache.v4/`)\n\nSQLite database containing:\n- File paths\n- File modification times\n- Extracted tags (functions, classes, methods) from tree-sitter parsing\n- Cross-file relationships\n\n---\n\n### 5. Session Resumption and Restore\n\n#### `--restore-chat-history` Flag\n\nWhen invoked with `--restore-chat-history`:\n1. Aider reads the `.aider.chat.history.md` file\n2. Parses the Markdown into message objects\n3. If history exceeds token limits, applies `ChatSummary` summarization\n4. Restores the conversation context\n\n**Source code from `aider/args.py`:**\n```python\ngroup.add_argument(\n    \"--restore-chat-history\",\n    action=argparse.BooleanOptionalAction,\n    default=False,\n    help=\"Restore the previous chat history messages (default: False)\",\n)\n```\n\n#### No Native Session Management\n\n**Important:** Aider does **NOT** have native session save/restore functionality like Claude Code or OpenCode. The chat history file is a log, not a session state that can be resumed.\n\nA community fork by Vikash Patel (github.com/vk4s/aider) added session management with:\n- `/session save <name>` - Save current session to `.aider/sessions/` as JSON\n- `/session load <name>` - Restore a saved session\n- `/session list` - List saved sessions\n- `/session view <name>` - View session contents\n- `/session delete <name>` - Delete a session\n\nThis was **never merged into upstream Aider**.\n\n---\n\n### 6. Comparison with Other Tools\n\n| Feature | Aider | Claude Code | OpenCode |\n|---------|-------|-------------|----------|\n| **Storage Format** | Markdown | JSONL | SQLite |\n| **Session Resumption** | Partial (restore flag) | Native (`--resume`) | Native (`--continue`) |\n| **Structured Data** | No (Markdown log) | Yes (JSONL events) | Yes (SQLite tables) |\n| **Searchable** | Via git grep | Via SQL/text | Via SQL |\n| **Location** | `<git_root>/.aider.chat.history.md` | `~/.claude/projects/` | `.opencode/` directories |\n\n---\n\n### 7. Summary\n\n- **Primary storage:** Markdown file at `<git_root>/.aider.chat.history.md`\n- **Format:** Human-readable Markdown transcript (not JSON, JSONL, or SQLite for chat history)\n- **In-memory format:** List of `{\"role\": \"...\", \"content\": \"...\"}` dictionaries\n- **No native session management** - chat history is append-only log, not resumable sessions\n- **Repository cache:** SQLite via `diskcache` in `.aider.tags.cache.v4/`\n- **Configuration:** YAML (`.aider.conf.yml`) and Dotenv (`.env`) files\n- **Session restoration:** Possible via `--restore-chat-history` flag with automatic summarization",
